"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063739","House of Commons Commission","false","2019-02-28","<p>Five of the ten apprentices from the 2017–2018 cohort secured roles at the House, with a sixth gaining a temporary role at the end of their apprenticeship before moving on to another employer.</p><p>This data was collected for the final cohort of apprentices graduating at the end of 2018 and will continue to be collected for future apprentices. Data for previous years is not held.</p>","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake",,"2019-02-28T13:47:25.1Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063739/answer","Biography information for Tom Brake","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063739/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063739/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2019-02-18","House of Commons: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington, representing the House of Commons Commission, what percentage of apprentices secured permanent employment in the House of Commons after completing their apprenticeships in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Robert Halfon","Harlow","Robert Halfon","222788"
