"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063752","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-02-21","<p>I replied to the hon. Member’s <a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2019-01-11/207610/" target="_blank">Question</a> on 18 February 2019</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2019-02-21T12:41:30.867Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063752/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063752/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063752/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-02-18","Department for Work and Pensions: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 16 January 2019 to Question 207610 on Social Security Benefits, when she plans to provide a substantive Answer to that Question.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","222687"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063753","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-02-22","<p>My officials meet regularly with officers of the Local Government Boundary Commission for England where a range of matters are discussed including the Government’s intentions for implementing proposals for new unitary councils. All such discussions are in the context of the Government’s clear recognition of the independence of the Commission and an appreciation of the Commission’s published guidance on electoral matters and its aim that electoral arrangements for councils should seek to be fair and deliver equality of representation for electors.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2019-02-22T15:09:21.84Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063753/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063753/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063753/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-02-18","Unitary Councils","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what recent discussions he has had with the Local Government Boundary Commission for England on establishing the optimum (a) size of electoral division and (b) number of elected councillors in each county division before the April 2020 vesting deadline for new unitary local authorities; and what the outcome was of those discussions.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","222688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063754","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-02-25","<p>The Government continues to work with industry to help manage economic impacts for the livestock sector in a no deal departure. Contingency options are being developed to respond to potential animal welfare issues on farm and during transport and these have been incorporated into broader Government no deal planning. There are no plans for a mass cull.</p><p> </p>","Macclesfield","David Rutley",,"2019-02-25T10:15:09.26Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063754/answer","Biography information for David Rutley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063754/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063754/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-02-18","Livestock: Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions he has had with Cabinet colleagues on contingency arrangements for the mass slaughter of livestock in the event that ports are closed if the UK leaves the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","222689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063755","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2019-02-20","<p>The Local Government Boundary Commission for England has no current plans to carry out a single programme of electoral reviews for all local authorities in England.</p><p>The Commission administers a rolling programme of electoral reviews and can include local authorities if they meet one or more of the following criteria:</p><ul><li>If a council has high levels of electoral inequality, where some councillors represent many more, or many fewer, voters than the average for the local authority area. The Commission targets authorities where the number of electors in 30% or more wards or divisions varies from the average of the council by 10% or more. Where one ward or division varies by 30% or more, the Commission will also consider carrying out a review. In both cases, the Commission will carry out a review if it believes the variances will not be corrected, without a review, within a reasonable period of time.</li><li>If a council has not undergone an electoral review in more than 12 years.</li><li>Where the Commission has been asked to carry out an electoral review.</li></ul><p>In the financial year 2019/20, the Commission plans to initiate electoral reviews in 25 English local authorities selected through the criteria set out above.</p>","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson",,"2019-02-20T14:02:00.833Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063755/answer","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063755/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063755/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2019-02-18","Local Government: Constituencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland South, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, what the timetable is for the full Boundary Review of local councils.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","222690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063756","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-02-21","<p>Records available show that annual payments by the Ministry of Defence to Serco Denholm Marine Services Limited under the original Future Provision of Marine Services contract, up to 31 December 2018, total £716 million.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2019-02-21T15:48:02.553Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063756/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063756/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1063756/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-02-18","Ministry of Defence: Serco-Denholm","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of annual payments made by his Department to Serco Denholm Marine Services Limited under the Future Provision of Marine Services contract to date.","false","Biography information for Mr Paul Sweeney","Glasgow North East","Mr Paul Sweeney","222691"
